channel.title: Public 3D printed parts
channel.description:
Hi everyone. I wanted to start a discussion to share models and thoughts on 3D printed parts that may be of use.
Here in GbG israel i designed a bunch of 3D parts, some we use in all builds and some only when required.
I would love to have any feedback on my own models and also hear from you guys what you use or would love to see modeled. What is the most time consuming task in your build?
Parts: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:5363913 https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4888212 https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3853387 https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3668860 Ping me if you need help printing
PS: We use https://www.logitechg.com/en-us/products/gamepads/adaptive-gaming-kit-accessories.943-000318.html for our bush buttons which have 3.5mm male mono plug.

Here in GbG israel i designed a bunch of 3D parts, some we use in all builds and some only when required.

I would love to have any feedback on my own models and also hear from you guys what you use or would love to see modeled.
What is the most time consuming task in your build?

Parts:

thingiverse.com

Audio plug holder (GoBabyGo israel) by houdini

Go baby go a non profit that fits electric cars for disabled kids. Designs are used to hold and connect a simple audio plug to the car dash, plug is used to connect a push button. https://www.gobabygo.org.il/

thingiverse.com

Connectors for Logitech adaptive gaming kit (GoBabyGo israel) by houdini

Go baby go a non profit that fits electric cars for disabled kids. Designs are used to connect push buttons easily to a car with a many configuration to fit the actual needs of the kids. Connectors are for the Logitech gaming kit push buttons. The...

thingiverse.com

PVC hindge (GoBabyGo israel) by houdini

Go baby go a non profit that fits electric cars for disabled kids. Design is used to move a tray down to the kids lap in the car and up to allow easy exit and enter. Hinge is used to move two peaces of PCV in a 360 degree range around a center pvc...

thingiverse.com

Push botton connector (GoBabyGo israel) by houdini

Go baby go a non profit that fits electric cars for disabled kids. Designs are used to connect push buttons easily to a car with a many configuration to fit the actual needs of the kids. Bottom replacement for big and small bottoms are replacement...

Ping me if you need help printing

PS:
We use Logitech G Adaptive Gaming Kit for the Xbox Adaptive Controller for our bush buttons which have 3.5mm male mono plug.
